data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 07, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zum1665702619077.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zum1665702619077.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zum1665702619077.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zum1665702619077\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Rename a Development\n      Object</h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can rename an object in-line in the Structure Editor, or in the Properties Inspector.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"zum1665702619077__context_w8949ab1b5b1_w8950ab1b5_w8951ab1\">The names of Uniface objects can be any combination of up to 60 alphanumeric\n         characters, including (A-Z, a-z), digits (0-9), and underscores (_), but must begin with a\n         letter. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eew1665702619155.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eew1665702619155.html\" title=\"The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database.\">Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects</a>.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zum1665702619077__note_owd_4cf_jzb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Although you can enter letters in lowercase, Uniface converts\n            these to uppercase, so you cannot use upper and lowercase letters to make names\n            unique.</div><p class=\"p\" id=\"zum1665702619077__p_d4010e1_d4011e1_d4012e1\">Use Windows conventions for renaming\n            files:</p></section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zum1665702619077__li_d1538e1_d1539e1_d1540e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zum1665702619077__p_d4013e1_d4014e1_d4015e1\">Click inside the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span>\n               property of an object. In the Structure Editor, you can right-click the object and\n               choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Rename</span> from the context menu.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zum1665702619077__li_d1541e1_d1542e1_d1543e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zum1665702619077__p_d4016e1_d4017e1_d4018e1\">Enter a new name for the object and press <span class=\"ph keypress\">Enter</span>.\n As you type, suggestions are provided when renaming an entity, field, or label. You can accept one of the suggestions or continue typing to give the object a new name.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zum1665702619077__li_d1544e1_d1545e1_d1546e1\">For entities, suggestions are for modeled\n                     entities.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zum1665702619077__li_d1547e1_d1548e1_d1549e1\">For fields, suggestions are offered only if\n                     the parent entity is modeled.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zum1665702619077__li_d1550e1_d1551e1_d1552e1\">For labels, suggestions are offered for all\n                     fields in the component, not just those of the current entity. Labels can be\n                     located outside an entity and can be associated with any field. Suggestions are\n                     in the format <var class=\"keyword varname\">Field.Entity</var>, which is the syntax for\n                     associated label names.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zum1665702619077__p_d4019e1_d4020e1_d4021e1\">If you enter a non-existing name for a modeled entity or field, it becomes non-modeled.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"zum1665702619077__fig_ard_vcf_jzb\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Renaming an entity</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Smart suggestions in renaming object\" class=\"image\" id=\"zum1665702619077__image_brd_vcf_jzb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/labelsuggestionsdsp.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zum1665702619077__p_d4022e1_d4023e1_d4024e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uoo1665702618603.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uoo1665702618603.html\" title=\"Smart suggestions are a Uniface feature that enable search and filtering functionality on the basis of object name and description. This makes it easier and faster to find an object that you want to open, edit, or use in a given context.\">Smart Suggestions and Filtering</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534621\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534621\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Rename a Development Object Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 07, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Rename a Development Object You can rename an object in-line in the Structure Editor, or in the Properties Inspector. The names of Uniface objects can be any combination of up to 60 alphanumeric characters, including (A-Z, a-z), digits (0-9), and underscores (_), but must begin with a letter. For more information, see Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects . Note: Although you can enter letters in lowercase, Uniface converts these to uppercase, so you cannot use upper and lowercase letters to make names unique. Use Windows conventions for renaming files: Click inside the Name property of an object. In the Structure Editor, you can right-click the object and choose Rename from the context menu. Enter a new name for the object and press Enter . As you type, suggestions are provided when renaming an entity, field, or label. You can accept one of the suggestions or continue typing to give the object a new name. For entities, suggestions are for modeled entities. For fields, suggestions are offered only if the parent entity is modeled. For labels, suggestions are offered for all fields in the component, not just those of the current entity. Labels can be located outside an entity and can be associated with any field. Suggestions are in the format Field.Entity , which is the syntax for associated label names. If you enter a non-existing name for a modeled entity or field, it becomes non-modeled. Figure 1. Renaming an entity For more information, see Smart Suggestions and Filtering . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}